description: Sofia discovers the incredible mystery behind her amulet. Princess Elena from the Kingdom of Avalor has been magically trapped inside Sofia's amulet, waiting for another Princess to set her free, and Sofia is up to the task!
synopsis_with_character_names:
In the Kingdom of Avalor, Elena takes Naomi up a mountain to show her her favorite view of the kingdom. Elena laments to Naomi how she was trapped in the Amulet of Avalor for forty-one years and then presents to her a broken wand. She tells her that it was Shuriki's wand and how she would still be trapped in the Amulet if it was not for a brave young princess: Sofia. Elena then proceeds to tell Naomi the whole story:

A coach is heading toward Avalor Palace. It is being chased by a green mist. When the coach reaches the castle, Elena comes out to greet her parents just in time to see a person come out of the mist who kills Elena's parents with a spell. The sorceress then proceeds to strike Elena with the same spell.

The attack is revealed to be a daydream that Sofia is having. Flora flies by and dismisses the students for summer vacation. As the Royal Kids of Enchancia heads back to the coach, Sofia's amulet starts to glow blue alerting her that it is time to go to the Secret Library.

Meanwhile, King Roland and Queen Miranda are trying to decide where to take their kids for their summer vacation. When the Royal Twins meet up with them, they reveal they still have not picked a place out. Meanwhile, Sofia grabs Behind the Walls and heads to the Secret Library.

When she arrives, the Library selects a book called "The Lost Princess of Avalor" to the shock of Sofia. When the book goes into the pendulem, it turns into a man known as Alacazar, the Royal Wizard of Avalor. He then proceeds to tell Sofia the story of The Lost Princess of Avalor, which is the tale of Princess Elena. On her fifteenth birthday, she was given the Amulet of Avalor by her mother. But on one fateful day, an evil power-hungry sorceress named Shuriki invaded Avalor. She attacked and murdered King Raul and Queen Lucia and set her sights on the palace. As the story goes, Elena chose to face Shuriki on her own. When Shuriki tried to strike her down, the Amulet saved Elena's life by pulling her inside it. Alacazar found the Amulet and discovered that the only way to free Elena was to find a special Princess to set her free. For years Alacazar searched for this princess until he grew too old to continue. He then used the last of his magic to turn himself into the book he transformed from. Alacazar also explains that over the years the Amulet has tested many princesses before her and up till now the Amulet has chosen Sofia to set Elena free, and the daydreams she has been having were Elena telling her the time has come to set her free. In order to free Elena, Sofia must go to Avalor and summon his chanul. Alakazar also warns Sofia to be careful as Shuriki is as powerful and evil as ever. Sofia goes to her family and convinces them they should spend their vacation in the Kingdom of Avalor. The Royal Family of Enchancia then sets sail for Avalor.

The Royal Family arrive on the Royal Galleon under the command of Admiral Vasquez. When Sofia sees Avalor City, she wonders how she is going to find Alacazar's house in such a huge city. Sofia is horrified to learn that they are going to meet Shuriki since Roland sent a message ahead telling her they were coming since it is the custom to greet the King or Queen when visiting a new Kingdom. Meanwhile, Shuriki is using her magic to get ready for their arrival when Chancellor Esteban comes in and informs her they have arrived. The Royal Family are greeted by cheering crowds but Sofia notices that the crowd is not actually happy. Shuriki arrives to greet them and Sofia is wary instantly. Sofia notices a flute playing to Shuriki's chagrin. As they get into the coach, Sofia spots Shuriki's guards take the flute from the boy playing it, upsetting him. They arrive at Avalor Palace where Shuriki gives them a tour before taking them out to a feast. Suddenly, winged jaguars known as Jaquins arrive and snatch some of the food. Shuriki is about to pull out her wand but Esteban stops her and leads the group back inside. Sofia's Amulet glows and pulls her toward the Jaquins which Sofia takes to mean they can help her. Sofia goes up to the Jaquins and asks for their help. The Jaquins refuse stating they do not help friends of Shuriki's. However, after hearing Sofia's plan to help bring Princess Elena back, the Jaquins instantly become delighted to help and take her to Alacazar's house.

Sofia arrives at Alacazar's house. A woman greets her but proves to be of no help when Sofia tells her why she is here. Suddenly, Alacazar's grandson Mateo walks up and asks Sofia about her magical knowledge and reveals that the woman is his mother. Sofia introduces herself and reveals Alacazar sent her. Mateo realizes that Sofia's Amulet is the Amulet of Avalor and takes her to his workshop. Once there, Mateo reveals that he has been training himself to be a wizard in secret since Shuriki outlawed all magic other than her own when she took over. He also reveals that a chanul is a spirit animal that acts as a guide to all the magical things in the world and that it was Alacazar's chanul who revealed to him of Elena's imprisonment in the Amulet and how to get her out. Mateo summons Alacazar's chanul, Zuzo, who tells Sofia what she has to do to free Elena from the Amulet: She has to get Shuriki's wand. Once she gets it, she has to wrap the amulet around it and put both on the Crown of Aziluna, a Maruvian healer who could undo any spell or curse and located in the mountains is a statue of him. After Zuzo vanishes, Sofia does not know how she is going to get Shuriki's wand until Mateo accidentally gives her an idea: To dance with her. At Avalor Palace, Armando is entertaining the Royal Twins while Shuriki's conversation with Roland and Miranda is having her contemplating invading Enchancia. Sofia comes in and convinces Shuriki to dance the sambarossa with her. After Armando has shown them how, everyone dances the sambarossa. During the dance, Sofia pretends to trip and steps on Shuriki's shoes. While Shuriki is recoiling from the pain, Sofia steals Shuriki's wand from her. After pocketing the wand, Sofia convinces Shuriki to let her and her siblings play hide and seek with Armando while she and her parents resume their discussions. When Armando starts counting, Sofia pulls her brother and sister away with her. Amber realizes that Sofia is up to something and asks her about it. Sofia promises her and James that she will explain everything later and right now needs them to stay hidden for as long as possible. James instantly agrees but Amber demands to know why Sofia will not tell them, only for her to say it is for their own good. Sofia heads back to Mateo and the Jaquins with the wand. Both are impressed with her for pulling it off and then the group then flies off to free Elena.

The group arrives at the Maruvian temple where the Crown of Aziluna is, and go inside to find a magical lake. For the magic to work, Sofia needs to swim across the enchanted waters. So Sofia turns herself into a mermaid and dives into the lake. Once underwater, she finds the Crown of Aziluna and does as Zuzo instructed. This causes an island with a statue on it to rise out of the water. Once it surfaces, Sofia slides down to the base of the statue. Suddenly, Sofia's amulet glows pink and descends. Once it hits the ground, a person appears in a flash of pink light. The Amulet returns itself to Sofia now pink. The person is revealed to be Princess Elena, who is finally free. Elena hugs Sofia and greets the Jaquins and Mateo. She then voices her intention to free Avalor from Shuriki. Upon leaving the temple, Elena tells the group of her plan: She is going to use Shuriki's wand against her. Sofia and Mateo want to help but she refuses and flies back to face Shuriki alone with Sofia and Mateo going after her anyway.

Armando is still playing hide and seek with Amber and James when Elena lands in the palace. Skylar wants to help but Elena tells him she has to do this alone. Elena confronts Shuriki in the throne room and tells Shuriki it is time to pay for her crimes, to Shuriki's horror. When Roland asks "What crimes?" Elena brings up how Shuriki invaded Avalor and seized the throne from the Royal Family of Avalor, her family. Shuriki tries to pull out her wand only to find out that Elena has it, which makes her deduce that Sofia took it. Miranda is shocked to learn of her daughter's involvement, which Elena confirms, while Shuriki has the Avalor Royal Guards arrest Roland and Miranda. Elena then tries to blast Shuriki, but only succeeds in blasting aside a tapestry that reveals a painting of Elena's little sister and grandparents. Shuriki reveals that was how Alacazar protected them: By placing them inside an enchanted painting even her magic cannot touch. She also reveals that Esteban is Elena's cousin, and then takes back her wand before ordering her guards to seize Elena. However, Skylar flies in and helps Elena escape. Shuriki orders her guards to throw Sofia's family into the dungeon and to capture Sofia and Elena. Roland orders Shuriki to leave Sofia alone and how she'll regret throwing his family in the dungeon, but Shuriki smugly replies that she doubts it. Elena meets up with Sofia and tells her that Shuriki has her family. Together, they fly back to Mateo's house.

When they arrive back at Mateo's house, Mateo's mother, Rafa, comes out and reveals the spell that can free Elena's family. Citizens of Avalor also come over and, at Sofia's urging, Elena agrees to let them help. Sofia and Elena fly to a secret entrance to the castle and sneak into the dungeon. Once inside, they meet Armando, who agrees to help. While Armando distracts the guard, Sofia sneaks past him using her shrinking ability. Sofia finds her family and lets them out. After locking up the guard, Elena explains everything to Roland and Miranda, who forgive Sofia for hiding her real intentions for visiting Avalor. The group then sets off to execute Elena's plan. Meanwhile, Shuriki demands that Esteban produce the results she desires. Esteban protests that when he helped her invade Avalor she promised no one in his family would get hurt to which Shuriki retorts that she also promised him power which she granted after appointing him Chancellor. Shuriki tells him to be grateful she kept one of her promises, or he will end up like his aunt and uncle, King Raul and Queen Lucia. Suddenly, Luna flies in and attacks Shuriki, who chases after her. Once Shuriki is gone, Mateo sneaks in and, using the spell his mother gave him, frees Elena's family, who happily reunite with Elena. The entire group then flies off to execute the next part of the plan: rallying the citizens of Avalor against Shuriki. The Avalorians and the Enchancians all march on the castle together and overwhelm the guards, who lock the gate.

Sofia and Elena fly in and open the gates while Roland keeps the guards busy, through which the Avalorians march through. Despite being outnumbered, and the royal guards fleeing like cowards, Shuriki still has her magic, and as Shuriki raises her wand to blast Elena, Esteban, who was pretending to serve Shuriki to protect his family from her, grabs Shuriki's wand and tosses it to Elena, who snaps it in two. With her wand broken, Shuriki's powers are destroyed and she ages into an old woman, and a horribly weakened Shuriki falls down a waterfall and swims away. Esteban then proclaims Elena is the rightful heir of Avalor. Sofia offers the amulet back to Elena, only to be told that Elena wants her to have it. Elena then assumes the throne of Avalor, to the joy of all the Avalorians. Back in the Secret Library, Sofia and Alacazar both review the story Sofia finished. She has given Elena's story a great ending which has also given her story a great beginning. After Alacazar vanishes, Sofia's dress undergoes a transformation and she leaves the Secret Library. Back in the present, Elena and Naomi both decide to lock Shuriki's wand away in the treasury forever and then head back to the palace together.

description: The new A-Troupe team results in one top dancer losing their spot. Emily is fighting to keep her spot as Dance Captain.
synopsis_with_character_names:
The new dancers for A-Troupe are announced. Returning members are Emily Stephanie, Tiffany, Riley, James and Eldon. New members joining from B-Troupe are Chloe, Daniel and West. New dancer Michelle is also a part of A-Troupe. Giselle, who was previously a member of A-Troupe and an E-girl, is kicked out and put in B-Troupe. Emily promises Giselle she will find a way to get her back.

As the B-Troupe dancers leave James' ex-girlfriend Beth, who didn't make it to A-Troupe, tells James she misses him, James believes she still likes him.

Emily passive aggressively tells Michelle she needs to work hard to be in A-Troupe, as she believes Michelle does not deserve to be there.

The E-Girls hang out in the juice bar Squeezed and tell new E-Girl Chloe about all the E-Girl rules. Giselle joins them and Emily pulls her aside to tell Giselle she cannot be a part of the E-Girls anymore, as someone has to be in A-Troupe to be an E-Girl. This bothers Riley, who thinks she's being unfair.

Giselle goes to Studio A to perform a solo, saying she got too comfortable and if she'd pushed herself more she wouldn't have lost her spot on A-Troupe.

Kate and Chris discuss the Dance Captain. Kate believes they should go with Emily again, but Chris thinks they should see what Michelle could bring to the studio, as she was Dance Captain at her last studio.

On their way to dance Giselle asks Riley if Emily knows what she's going to do to help Giselle get back in to A-Troupe. Riley says Emily doesn't have a plan yet.

While Eldon teaches a Baby Ballet class, James struggles with his maths homework. He asks Eldon for help but isn't able to get it.

The E-Girls talk about going shopping as E-Girl rule number 15 is if one E-Girl goes shopping, they all go shopping. Chloe has to pay for dance so can't afford to buy things, but doesn't tell the others. Emily is unhappy that Chloe is already breaking the rules. Michelle sits down with them and Emily is confused as they aren't friends and tells her the seat is for Riley so she has to move. She sits with West who comforts her.

Michelle waits outside Studio B, as Stephanie told her A-Troupe rehearsal is there. Giselle arrives and tells her she should go to Studio A. Michelle apologises to Giselle, for 'taking her spot' but Giselle tells her it's okay, because she's a very good dancer and to be careful with the E-Girls. Giselle goes into B-Troupe rehearsal where the dancers are all messing around, Giselle sees how much she doesn't fit in.

Michelle arrives late for A-Troupe rehearsal, Kate and Chris are disappointed about this. She says she got lost rather than tell them Stephanie lied.

Kate and Chris announce that they're going to pick Dance Captain. Emily thinks they're going to vote and it'll be her, but Kate and Chris say Michelle will have a chance of being Dance Captain too. Michelle reluctantly agrees to audition. Emily isn't happy but is willing to take on Michelle as she really wants Dance Captain.

description: The A-Troupe is split in two to test the leadership of the competing Dance Captains.
synopsis_with_character_names:
To establish Dance Captain the team will be split into two groups, Emily and Michelle will both choreograph a dance, the best dance will decide Dance Captain. Emily wants to work with her E-Girls but Chris decides the teams, splitting them up. He puts Chloe, Daniel, Tiffany and Eldon with Emily and Stephanie, James, Riley and West with Michelle. Emily's team will rehearse in Studio A while Michelle's will rehearse in Studio B.

In Squeezed, West challenges James to a dance battle, by dancing at him. James is freaked out and leaves.

Stephanie reveals to the other dancers that Michelle is Miss National Soloist. The others are very impressed and Michelle tells them she's won Nationals. Emily's team start rehearsing while Michelle's team do a fun warm up exercise. Stephanie refuses to participate.

Chloe tells Emily she has to leave because she has a shift at her job. Emily doesn't let her leave.

Michelle's team decide their dance is good and they should go home, while Emily's exhausted team has to stay and keep practicing. Emily sees Riley as she's leaving and goes to ask about Michelle's dance. Riley reassures her and Emily asks to be kept informed. Riley doesn't like how threatened Emily is, and is worried how it will affect the team.

James mum comes into the studio to talk to Chris about him struggling in school, especially maths. She says she wants to pull him from the studio, and Chris says he'll help James with maths as he's worried how James leaving will affect the team.

In Squeezed, Stephanie tells the rest of the E-Girls she has a plan to prevent Michelle winning Dance Captain. Riley is very concerned what this is.

Chloe and Daniel tell West they are very tired from Emily overworking them. James arrives and West dances at him again. James doesn't join in and leaves.

Kate and Chris ask Emily and Michelle how their dances are coming along, Emily asks for more time but Michelle says she's ready. This annoys Emily and Kate and Chris decide they've had enough time and they should perform.

Emily performs first and her dance goes well. When Michelle performs, Stephanie deliberately dances badly to ruin Michelle's chances. Afterwards Stephanie lies and says she just hadn't rehearsed enough.

Riley tells off Emily and Stephanie, Emily accuses her of not being a real E-Girl as she is breaking the number one rule, an E-Girl always has another E-Girl's back.

Chris still has faith in Michelle as Dance Captain, but they end up choosing Emily. This causes a fight to break out within the group.

Chris leaves and comes back with a bucket of ping pong balls which he throws onto the floor to clean up, to force them to work as a team.

While clearing them up, West dances at James again. This time James joins in, and then everyone else starts dancing too, bringing them back together as a team.

description: When mate asks Emily to hold dance evaluation placements in the group dance, Emily decides to put Michelle in the back row to cause waves amongst the dancers
synopsis_with_character_names:
Kate announces the dancers are going to compete in a local dance competition and she would like to change the line placements. The dancers will have to audition for her and Chris to decide the placements. Emily wants to make the decision, as she's Dance Captain, so convinces them she should do it.

Daniel is planning to choreograph a dance for J-Troupe, to freak him out Tiffany tells him they're 'crazy', because E-Girl rule number 46 is never let anyone else in A-Troupe look too good.

The A-Troupe dancers perform for Emily, Riley messes up her dance so believes she'll be in the back row. Emily is very critical of Michelle's audition. The other dancers think Michelle should be in the front row.

Emily and Stephanie go into Kate's office and pretend that they're checking the line placements with them, when really they're telling Kate about a light bulb that went out.

Emily puts Michelle in the back row and then puts Riley in the front row. This makes Riley suspicious as she doesn't think she deserves front row. They perform their routine and Riley struggles as she isn't used to being in the front row. Emily calls a break for everyone so Riley can have a moment and doesn't listen when Riley explains that she shouldn't be in the front row.

Daniel is very nervous choreographing for J-Troupe because of Tiffany. Tiffany told them if they were difficult for him they can perform for A-Troupe, so they pick on him and are deliberately slow to learn the steps.

Riley asks James if he thinks she should be in the front row, and he tells her he thinks Michelle should. Riley is sad because she hoped maybe he believed in her. James tells Riley he got her something 'from the top of a mountain' and gives her mountain spring water.

Tiffany turns up to help him with the J-Troupe who start co-operating, making Daniel like her.

Riley goes to see Kate to ask her why she approved the line-up with Michelle in the back and her in the front. Kate reveals she didn't have anything to do with it. Riley goes to talk to Emily about it and Emily gets angry that Riley isn't accepting Emily did something nice for her.

Back in rehearsal Riley tells James that Kate didn't approve the dance placements and that she has an idea of something to do. James encourages her to do it. As they get in position to dance Riley moves Michelle to the front and stands in the back. Riley tells everyone Kate didn't approve the line placements. She asks the group if they agree that Michelle should be in the front row, James, Daniel and West speak up to say yes. Emily concedes and lets Michelle dance in the front. Kate comes and tells Emily well done for moving Michelle to the front.

J-Troupe perform for A-Troupe and their dance goes well.

Afterwards Riley goes over to the E-Girls and Emily tells her she thinks Riley hasn't been loyal enough to the E-Girls and asks the others if they want her out. They all vote yes and Riley is no longer an E-Girl.

description: On a day off, some of the dancers go to the beach while some stay in the studio.
synopsis_with_character_names:
While rehearsing their regionals routine Kate and Chris tell the group that due to dance camp being held in the studio they get a day off. Michelle suggests they should spend the day off at the beach. Emily says that the E-Girls have to help out with dance camp. Riley asks Emily if she wants her to join and Emily rejects her.

At the beach, Michelle compliments Riley's necklace, which she says was a gift from her grandma to Emily and Riley is borrowing it.

At dance camp, Chloe is struggling as she isn't comfortable around little kids.

The group at the beach combine dancing and playing frisbee. After a while Riley realises she's lost Emily's necklace. The group look around the beach and ask other people if they've seen it.

At dance camp Emily realises one of the children, Margie, is missing. She leaves Chloe responsible while she and the other E-Girls search the studio. Chloe is very awkward with them.

At the beach, James spots a man with a metal detector and asks him if they can borrow it to find the necklace. He says they can, if they give him a hundred dollars. Michelle says she has an idea to get the money.

At dance camp, Margie appears again in Studio A, where Chloe and the other kids are. Emily comes back relieved to see Margie is safe and is proud that Chloe coped with looking after the kids.

At the beach, the group dances for an audience who give them money. They have made the hundred dollars they need and go get the metal detector. After a bit of searching they find the necklace.

Back at the studio James compliments Emily's necklace and the group from the beach all laugh. Riley is annoyed because she doesn't want Emily to find out it was lost

description: To prepare for the competition, Emily convinces the team to go and spy on their arch enemies at Elite Dance Academy. Back at the studio, West and Daniel fight over studio space.
synopsis_with_character_names:
Emily, Stephanie and Tiffany return from a trio competition in which they placed second. They were beaten by Elite Dance Studio, The Next Step's rival. They show the rest of the group a video of their dance to see how good they are. Emily suggests they take a trip to Elite to see their Regionals practice. Riley offers to go but Emily turns her down. Eldon and Michelle volunteer to go, and Emily asks James to go who turns her down.

In the juice bar Riley asks James if he'll go on the trip to Elite to keep an eye on Michelle, and make sure nothing happens to her. He agrees but says she owes him.

Daniel goes to Studio A to rehearse. While he's there Beth asks about James, which amuses him. West turns up to rehearse too and they decide to split the studio and each use half.

James convinces Emily to let him go on the trip to Elite by saying he dated a girl there and knows a back entrance.

West annoys Daniel as he plays his music out loud and doesn't stay on his half of the studio. Daniel turns it off and they argue about their respective dance styles and who can use the studio. West comes up with the idea that they choreograph for each other. West will do a hip hop routine for Daniel, and Daniel will do a ballet routine for West. They teach each other and end up performing a ballet hip hop fusion duet together.

Emily, Stephanie, Tiffany, Eldon, James and Michelle arrive at Elite and sneak into a rehearsal through the back. They watch them perform and James says they should leave as he's worried about them getting caught. Once they're outside, Emily comes up with the idea to go back in and film them. Michelle volunteers because she wants Emily to accept her. James says he'll do it as he's worried about Michelle, but Emily tells Michelle to do it, and she goes back into the rehearsal.

Worried about how long Michelle is taking, Emily texts her. Michelle's phone goes off alerting the Elite dancers, who call her over. Emily tells Stephanie to go in and see whats happening. Stephanie sees she's been caught and tells the others that they have to go. James protests but Emily forces him into the car and they abandon Michelle

description: An interstellar princess is exiled to earth and teams up with a teenage boy to battle villains from her universe.
tags: ['birthday', 'new kid in school', 'interrogation', 'puppy']
synopsis_with_character_names:
Star Comes to Earth -


On her 14th Birthday, Star Butterfly eagerly accepts her mother's magic wand. Though cautioned to take care of it, lest it fall into the hands of evil, Star claims she can handle her new responsibilities...but within seconds, the kingdom is plunged into chaos!

Star fears she'll be sent to St Olga's Reform School for Wayward Princesses, but her parents claim they are sending her to the Earth dimension 'to train.'

Enrolling Star in Echo Creek Academy, a student named Marco Diaz is assigned to guide her around, as many claim him to be 'the safe kid,' something Marco vehemently denies.

At first, Marco thinks Star's strangeness will only be found at school, but upon arriving home, he finds that she will be staying with his family as well.

Showing her to her room, Marco is shocked when her magic wand turns her simple bedroom into a 3-story, turreted structure. When Marco tells how he wishes he had a similar room, Star eagerly goes to his to do the same. However, her magic spell of 'mystic room suck transform,' opens a black hole in the room, sucking in everything!

Marco gets mad at the destruction of his room, and Star attempts to cheer him up, but Marco frustratingly leaves the house.

Catching up to Marco some time later, Star apologizes for her actions, willing to move out. However, the moment is broken when some monsters led by a bird-creature named Ludo, intervene. Ludo and his minions attempt to take Star's wand from her, but are waylaid by its powers, along with Marco's karate skills.

The group is soon over-powered, and return to their dimension. Realizing that he may have overreacted, Marco decides he is okay with Star staying with him and his family.

Party With a Pony -


Marco is all set to spend an evening eating nachos with Star, when they receive a visit from Star's friend from Mewni: Flying Princess Ponyhead! However, Ponyhead is a little perturbed at finding out her best friend Star, considers Marco to be a best friend as well. Ponyhead wishes to go out, and using her dimensional scissors, the group begins to dimension-hop.

The group then head to The Bounce Lounge dimension, where Ponyhead threatens Marco, and almost pushes him over the edge of the cloudy dimension. Star apologizes for her friend's actions, and recommends they all go to The Amethyst Arcade!

At the arcade, Ponyhead catches a glimpse of some hooded figures, and quickly recommends that Star and her go on to another dimension, with Ponyhead claiming that Marco went on ahead.

However, when Star finds her friend lied to her, she demands they go back for Marco.

Back in the arcade, Marco has been captured and is being interrogated by the masked figures. Star is about to intervene, when Ponyhead gives her her dimensional scissors, and catches the attention of the masked figures.

The group is cornered, when a booming voice is head, and Ponyhead's father, King Ponyhead, appears. It turns out the men in masks have come for Ponyhead, as she is being sent to St Olga's Reform School for Wayward Princesses. However, she wanted one last night of fun with her BFF. Star happily thanks her friend for coming back to save Marco, and even Marco forgives her.

After the group leaves, Star reveals she still has her friend's dimensional scissors, and they can go anywhere they want...but after all that's happened, Star and Marco end up just sitting on the couch, eating nachos.

description: Monster Arm: Star accidentally turns Marco's arm into a monster arm when he has to do karate. The Other Exchange Student: Star is jealous when the family's best friend shows up.
tags: ['karate', 'two word title', 'four word title']
synopsis_with_character_names:
Monster Arm -


Marco is looking forward to a karate tournament, where he hopes to show up a rich and privileged student named Jeremy Birnbaum. However, he ends up breaking his hand.

Noting Star's magic wand, Marco requests her to use a magic spell to heal his hand. Using her wand's instruction manual, she attempts to heal Marco, but instead turns his entire right arm into a 'monster arm/tentacle.'

The arm at first seems temperamental, but seems to open doors for Marco, when it stops bully from picking on a nerd, and Marco is hailed as a hero.

Later that evening, Star manages to find a reversal spell, but spends all night trying to perfect it. When she finally does, Marco claims he'd like to keep his new arm, sure that it can help him beat Jeremy. When Star claims that this might not be a good idea, Marco orders her to leave.

After he's done so, a spike-toothed mouth opens on the tentacle, and the sentient appendage fills Marco's head with dreams of defeating Jeremy, and even getting his secret crush Jackie Lynn Thomas to like him.

At the tournament, Star comes, but falls asleep from her last few days trying to find a cure. Marco's tentacle arm makes quick work of Jeremy, but then the arm demands that Marco rip out Jeremy's bowels. When Marco refuses, the arm begins to beat up on Marco. Star manages to wake up, and after some time, manages to return Marco's arm to normal...but not before it claims that it is a part of him now.

In the aftermath, it's also found out that Jeremy cheated, as he had brass(gold) knuckles in his boxing gloves, leaving the tournament with no winner.

After all is said and done, Marco's hand returns to being broken, with the possibility that Star's cure may not have truly excised the evil consciousness of the Monster Arm.

The Other Exchange Student -


The Diaz's have celebrated Star Butterfly's arrival everyday since she has come to live with them, but one day, a former exchange student named Gustav arrives! Gustav has come back from Scandinavia, and brought the Diaz's souvenirs. He also cooks meatballs for them, to which they all seem eager to eat.

The next day, Star grows jealous when it seems the family has forgotten her...when she finds some strange books in Gustav's backpack, one of which tells about learning the Scandinavian language. After seeing how Gustav also likes to make sure the Diaz family is eating plenty of food, Star grows more suspicious.

Feigning sleep, Star begins to follow Gustav, soon believing he intends to eat the family! She attempts to tell Marco, who simply thinks she's lost her mind.

The Diaz family heads to Isolation Point, but Star diverts them, and confronts Marco, scaring him out of his wits with her magic. However, he confesses that he is not actually Scandinavian, but an American boy named Charlie Booth, who comes from a boring town. He assumed the identity of Gustav, and has dreams of one day becoming a famous chef, which explains his food preparation skills.

Eventually, the Diaz family finds Gustav and Star, who does not blow Charle's cover...on condition that he leave and never come back to the Diaz household.

Gustav complies, and life returns to normal for Star, with the family returning to celebrating her being with them.

The final image show Charlie Booth, taking on the identity of a French Exchange Student named Francois, and going to another family, who happily welcome him in.

description: Star starts sprouting hearts all over her body, the telltale sign of "Mewberty." Marco and his friends travel to a dimension of pixies and are forced to work in the Shard Mines.
synopsis_with_character_names:
-Mewberty-

After art class, Marco notices a purple heart on Star's forehead. However, this causes Star to freak out, claiming this is the first sign she's beginning to go through: Mewberty.

Marco attempts to take Star home, but on her way out of the classroom, the sight of numerous boys causes more purple hearts to break out on her face and arms! Things get even weirder when a sticky purple growth extends from Star's arm, and attaches her to a locker! Star hides inside, while Marco goes to look for her wand's instruction manual.

Though Star let their friend Ferguson borrow it, he then loaned it to a school girl named Janna. Marco manages to get the book from her, but is unable to find anything about Mewberty. Wishing the book had a glossary, his words bring forth a small yellow-robed, blue-skinned creature from within the book, who calls himself, "Glossaryck of Terms."

Though Glossaryck claims he is only to take orders from Star, he is willing to grant Marco an exception of help...if Marco will provide him with pudding.

Marco does so, but all Glossaryck seems willing to tell him, is to let Mewberty run its course.

Leaving the manual behind, Marco comes across several boys cocooned in some nearby lockers, and sees Star: now purple-skinned, with six arms, and wings! Marco attempts to reason with her, but she begins to cocoon him too...before hearing the musical keyboard of her crush, Oskar Greeson.

Marco attempts to stop her, but his plan to throw a net over Star doesn't work, as she fights against it. Thinking back to what Glossaryck said about letting the symptoms 'run their course,' Marco lets go of the net...leaving Star to carry Oskar and his car into the clouds above.

As Marco laments losing Star...a rain of black-and-white hearts rain down, before Oskar and his car slam to the ground...followed shortly thereafter by Star.

She appears to be back to normal, except for two small 'mewberty' wings on her back. When Marco inquires if this means she can fly, she attempts to do so...but falls down.

-Pixtopia-

Marco, Alfonzo, and Ferguson are using Star's magic mirror to make dimensional prank calls. When Star decides to get in on the fun, a message from her service provider tells that she has exceeded her minute usage, requesting she come to Pixtopia to pay the bill.

Marco feels bad for what he did, but Star ribs him, claiming how he 'messed up.' Marco tries to forget this, and leads the group into Pixtopia, courtesy of Star's dimensional scissors.

Going to the Pixie Management Office, Marco's case is considered useless, as Pixies only accept gold or jewels. The group is then sent to the Shard Mines to work off the bill. Star attempts to use her want on the guards, but her magic doesn't work in the mines.

Ferguson attempts to stand up to the guard, and is led to the Pixie Empress for his disobedience. However, the Empress claims Ferguson "looks delicious," and gigglingly shows an interest in him!

Meanwhile, the others have commandeered a mine car, and escaped from the mines, straight into the Empress' castle, where Ferguson claims he and the Empress are about to be wed!

Marco manages to break Ferguson out of this thought, and the young man tells the Empress he isn't mature enough to make such a commitment...leading for the Empress to declare the group be killed.

Luckily, Star is able to lead everyone out, and back to her room (where she claims the experience has made her consider switching 'service providers'). Marco laments he may have denied his friend the chance to find love, but Star tells that the Empress was intending to eat Ferguson after they were wed.

It is then they realize that Alfonzo is not among them. The audience then finds out he has wed the Pixie Empress, promising to be a tyrannical king!
